.SH NAME
noti \- monitor a process and trigger a notification
.SH SYNOPSIS
noti [flags] [utility [args\&...]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Never sit and wait for some long\-running process to finish.
Noti can alert you when it\[cq]s done.
You can receive messages on your computer or phone.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-t <string>, \-\-title <string>
Set notification title.
Default is utility name.
.TP
\-m <string>, \-\-message <string>
Set notification message.
Default is \[lq]Done!\[rq].
Read from stdin with \[lq]\-\[rq].
.TP
\-b, \-\-banner
Trigger a banner notification.
This is enabled by default.
To disable this service, set this flag to false.
This will be either \f[CR]nsuser\f[R], \f[CR]freedesktop\f[R], or
\f[CR]notifyicon\f[R] notification, depending on the OS.
.TP
\-s, \-\-speech
Trigger a speech notification.
This will be either \f[CR]say\f[R], \f[CR]espeak\f[R], or
\f[CR]speechsynthesizer\f[R] notification, depending on the OS.
.TP
\-c, \-\-bearychat
Trigger a BearyChat notification.
This requires \f[CR]bearychat.incomingHookURI\f[R] to be set.
.TP
\[en]keybase
Trigger a Keybase notification.
This requires \f[CR]keybase.conversation\f[R] to be set.
.TP
\-p, \-\-pushbullet
Trigger a Pushbullet notification.
This requires \f[CR]pushbullet.accessToken\f[R] to be set.
.TP
\-o, \-\-pushover
Trigger a Pushover notification.
This requires \f[CR]pushover.apiToken\f[R] and
\f[CR]pushover.userKey\f[R] to be set.
.TP
\-u, \-\-pushsafer
Trigger a Pushsafer notification.
This requires \f[CR]pushsafer.key\f[R] to be set.
.TP
\-l, \-\-simplepush
Trigger a Simplepush notification.
This requires \f[CR]simplepush.key\f[R] to be set.
.TP
\-n,\-\-gchat
Trigger a Google Chat notification.
This requires \f[CR]gchat.appurl\f[R] to be set.
.TP
\-i,\-\-chanify
Trigger a Chanify notification.
This requires \f[CR]chanify.channelURL\f[R] to be set.
.TP
\-k, \-\-slack
Trigger a Slack notification.
This requires \f[CR]slack.appurl\f[R] (for Slack apps) or
\f[CR]slack.token\f[R] and \f[CR]slack.channel\f[R] (for legacy tokens)
to be set.
.TP
\[en]twilio
Trigger a Twilio notification.
This requires \f[CR]twilio.authToken\f[R], \f[CR]twilio.accountSid\f[R],
\f[CR]twilio.numberFrom\f[R] and \f[CR]twilio.numberTo\f[R] to be set.
.TP
\[en]ntfy
Trigger a ntfy notification.
This requires \f[CR]ntfy.topic\f[R] be set.
Optionally, \f[CR]ntfy.url\f[R] can also be set to use a different Ntfy
server.
.TP
\-w , \-\-pwatch 
Monitor a process by PID and trigger a notification when the pid
disappears.
.TP
\-f, \-\-file
Path to \f[CR]noti.yaml\f[R] configuration file.
.TP
\-\-verbose
Enable verbose mode.
.TP
\-v, \-\-version
Print \f[CR]noti\f[R] version and exit.
.TP
\-h, \-\-help
Print \f[CR]noti\f[R] help and exit.
