.SH EXAMPLES
Display a notification when \f[CR]tar\f[R] finishes compressing files.
.IP
.EX
noti tar \-cjf music.tar.bz2 Music/
.EE
.PP
Add noti after a command, in case you forgot at the beginning.
.IP
.EX
clang foo.c \-Wall \-lm \-L/usr/X11R6/lib \-lX11 \-o bizz; noti
.EE
.PP
If you already started a command, but forgot to use \f[CR]noti\f[R],
then you can do this to get notified when that process\[cq] PID
disappears.
.IP
.EX
noti \-\-pwatch $(pgrep docker\-machine)
.EE
